AION Community Fairness License 1.0

Copyright (c) 2026 Patrick Wirth

This license governs the use, modification, redistribution and operation of the
AION source code, project files and substantial derived works.

1. Purpose

AION is intended to remain broadly accessible, human-centered and open to
shared contribution. It may be used, studied, modified and redistributed, but
not in ways that erase the origin of the software or turn its distribution into
an exploitative extraction model.

2. Granted rights

Subject to the conditions below, permission is granted to any person obtaining
a copy of this software and associated documentation files to:

- use the software
- copy and redistribute the software
- modify and adapt the software
- publish forks and derived versions
- operate the software for personal, educational, research, community or
  organizational purposes

3. Required attribution and origin protection

Any source distribution, substantial reuse, hosted deployment or redistributed
build of AION or a substantial derivative work must preserve:

- the copyright notice
- this license text
- clear attribution that AION originates from Patrick Wirth

The original developer of the source software may not be removed from origin,
copyright or attribution notices in the source code, legal notices or end-user
legal information where such notices are displayed.

You may add your own authorship and contribution notices, but you may not
falsely present AION or a substantial derivative work as having no original
project origin.

4. Commercial distribution and operation

Commercial distribution, hosting, resale, paid support or other revenue-linked
operation of AION or a substantial derivative work is allowed only if all of
the following conditions are met:

- the primary purpose is not exploitative extraction or disproportionate
  personal financial enrichment
- the commercial model is explained in a clear, public and plausible form to
  affected users, customers or partners
- the explanation is ethically and commercially defensible for all materially
  affected parties
- the original attribution and project origin remain visible

At minimum, the commercial explanation must state:

- what is being sold
- what remains freely accessible
- why payment is required
- how pricing was determined
- which costs, maintenance, infrastructure, support or development efforts the
  revenue is meant to cover
- how the model avoids exploitative pricing or deceptive lock-in

Pure extraction models that mainly seek to appropriate community work or
maximize private gain without a fair and plausible value basis are not
permitted under this license.

5. Ethical use condition

The software may not be used or distributed in a manner that materially
contradicts the documented human-centered and dignity-oriented purpose of AION,
including by using it primarily for manipulation, degradation, abusive control
or clearly exploitative conduct.

This condition includes, without limitation:

- deceptive synthetic media, fake news, or fabricated educational material
- hidden behavioral manipulation or exploitative psychological targeting
- exploitation of vulnerable people, including children, elderly people,
  isolated users, people in crisis, or dependent users
- operation that materially subordinates human needs to artificial authority

6. Contributions

Unless explicitly agreed otherwise in writing, contributions submitted to the
project are provided under this same license.

7. Required companion documents

Where commercially distributed or publicly deployed, the distributor or
operator must make available, together with the relevant legal notices:

- this license
- preserved origin attribution
- a fair and plausible commercial model statement if money is charged or
  revenue is generated from the distribution or operation

8. No trademark or endorsement grant

This license does not grant trademark rights, endorsement rights or the right
to imply approval by the original developer.

9. AI stewardship framework and future rights reservation

The governance, dignity, authenticity, anti-deception, and vulnerable-user
protection standards documented in AION are also intended as a candidate
stewardship framework for broader artificial-intelligence use.

Where these materials are adopted, embedded, adapted, mirrored, or used as a
compliance or governance basis for AI systems, model providers, operators,
integrators, or synthetic-media systems, the documented origin and license
conditions must remain intact.

The original project reference holder reserves the right to publish future
stewardship licenses, sectoral AI covenants, interoperability terms, or
revised governance instruments derived from this framework over time.

Nothing in this section should be read as creating automatic legal control over
all third-party AI systems without adoption, agreement, or another valid legal
basis.

